<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFB7EF74FF12F886FD76F866" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF12F886FD76F866" blockId="31.[151,1436,1843,2014]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Twenty-four species within 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB7EF74FE52F886FDE0F8F5" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[471,597,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Odonturini">Odonturini</taxonomicName>
, belonging to six genera, are currently recognized in the Neotropical Region (
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB7EF74FF5DF8E2FE08F8C9" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[216,445,1879,1905]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref30789" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // orthoptera. speciesfile. org (accessed 13 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FEC4F8E2FECCF8C9" box="[321,377,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
). This tribe, however, seems only to include the Ethiopic genus 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB7EF74FB0CF8E2FA29F8C9" authority="Rambur, 1838" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1838" box="[1161,1436,1879,1905]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Odontotremataceae" genus="Odontura" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FB0CF8E2FB43F8C9" box="[1161,1270,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Odontura</emphasis>
Rambur, 1838
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB7EF74FF24F8CEFE26F82D" author="Grzywacz, B. &amp; Lehmann, A. W. &amp; Chobanov, D. P. &amp; Lehmann, G. U. C." box="[161,403,1915,1941]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="327 - 339" refId="ref32763" refString="Grzywacz, B., Lehmann, A. W., Chobanov, D. P. &amp; Lehmann, G. U. C. (2018) Multiple origin of flightlessness in Phaneropterinae bushcrickets and redefinition of the tribus Odonturini (Orthoptera: Tettigonioidea: Phaneropteridae). Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution, 18 (3), 327 - 339. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13127 - 018 - 0370 - x" type="journal article" year="2018">
Grzywacz 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FE9CF8CEFEE5F82D" box="[281,336,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), and the Neotropical species will probably be placed in its own tribe (O. Cadena-Castañeda, 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF12F82AFEAAF800" box="[151,287,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">pers. comm.</emphasis>
to MF). We found four species that were recently recorded and/or described from individuals collected at the Iguaçu National Park (
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB7EF74FE5DF876FD02F866" author="Fianco, M. &amp; Preis, H. &amp; Szinwelski, N. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Faria, L. R. R." box="[472,695,1987,2014]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="240 - 264" refId="ref32415" refString="Fianco, M., Preis, H., Szinwelski, N., Braun, H. &amp; Faria, L. R. R. (2019 b) On brachypterous phaneropterine katydids (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae) from the Iguacu National Park, Brazil: three new species, new record and bioacoustics. Zootaxa, 4652 (2), 240 - 264. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4652.2.2" type="journal article" year="2019">
Fianco 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FDA8F876FDD0F865" box="[557,613,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2019b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
